ABC7s Vaccine Tracker shows that at least 1.5 million people across Chicago are fully vaccinated for COVID-19 as of Sep.5, according to the most recent data made available by the city. At least 1.6 million Chicagoans have received one dose of the vaccine.

The latest city data shows about 55.8% of people living in Chicago are fully vaccinated.

The number of first doses given so far amount to about 61.1% of people in the city.

You can look up the progress thus far of vaccination of people in every Chicago zip code below. You can see the most-vaccinated zip codes in the table or search the map below to find the progress so far in your part of the city.

Where can I get vaccinated?

At least 1,767 pharmacies, medical facilities and other providers have vaccines in stock across Illinois. You can search all of them in our live map, which pulls data every morning from the VaccineFinder system at the CDCs vaccines.gov.

The yellow and green circles show clusters of locations. If you click them, the map will zoom in to show individual locations. Clicking a red marker will show the vaccine locations name, address and ways to get more information online or by phone.

You can use the search button at top right to zoom to your address or zip code.
